        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2439031780" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13719787288422625496">I adored this series when I was a kid, and I was in the mood for some comfort food reading, and deeply curious to see whether reading it would still hold any pleasure for me decades later. I’m happy to say that it did indeed hold many pleasures. There is an abiding sense of compassion and humor coursing through this book, even as its band of misfit adventurers face peril and hardship. It never reaches the poetic heights of Le Guin’s Earthsea Trilogy, another classic of children’s fantasy literat</span>
  <span id="freeText13719787288422625496" style="display:none">I adored this series when I was a kid, and I was in the mood for some comfort food reading, and deeply curious to see whether reading it would still hold any pleasure for me decades later. I’m happy to say that it did indeed hold many pleasures. There is an abiding sense of compassion and humor coursing through this book, even as its band of misfit adventurers face peril and hardship. It never reaches the poetic heights of Le Guin’s Earthsea Trilogy, another classic of children’s fantasy literature, but it ceaselessly entertains and enchants nonetheless. Alexander was especially adept at creating indelibly individual characters, most especially the hilarious, courageous, talkative, wise Eilonwy.<br /><br />I look forward to making my way through the rest of the series.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13719787288422625496" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


