<div id="review_2782767353" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2782767353" />
    <a title="Maria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/35190712-maria"><img alt="Maria" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1522512518p2/35190712.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2782767353?book_show_action=true">Apr 30, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maria" href="/user/show/35190712-maria">Maria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35190712-maria?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35190712-maria?shelf=high-fantasy">high-fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35190712-maria?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35190712-maria?shelf=zombies">zombies</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35190712-maria?shelf=band">band</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35190712-maria?shelf=children-s">children-s</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35190712-maria?shelf=journey">journey</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35190712-maria?shelf=dark">dark</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35190712-maria?shelf=coming-of-age">coming-of-age</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35190712-maria?shelf=adventure">adventure</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2782767353" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7529010844279376859">Taran wants to be a great warrior the likes of Gwydion, the greatest war leader in Prydain, but is stuck with pig-keeping and making horseshoes. <br/><br/><i>&apos;Why? Why must it be horseshoes?’ . . . ‘I wish I might have my own sword,&apos; Taran sighed. &apos;And you would teach me sword-fighting.&apos; <br/><br/>&apos;Wisht!&apos; cried Coll. &apos;Why should you want to know that? As if we had any battles at Caer Dallben.&apos;<br/><br/><b>&apos;We have no horses, either,&apos; </b> objected Taran.</i><br/><br/>But adventure ensues when psychic pig Hen Wen runs away, and must be found before</span>
  <span id="freeText7529010844279376859" style="display:none">Taran wants to be a great warrior the likes of Gwydion, the greatest war leader in Prydain, but is stuck with pig-keeping and making horseshoes. <br /><br /><i>'Why? Why must it be horseshoes?’ . . . ‘I wish I might have my own sword,' Taran sighed. 'And you would teach me sword-fighting.' <br /><br />'Wisht!' cried Coll. 'Why should you want to know that? As if we had any battles at Caer Dallben.'<br /><br /><b>'We have no horses, either,' </b> objected Taran.</i><br /><br />But adventure ensues when psychic pig Hen Wen runs away, and must be found before she can end up in the evil Horned King’s clutches.<br /><br />This was a fun little adventure and though middle-grade, it could get pretty dark (which I loved). I did not expect the characters to be so well-done, and quite enjoyed the world building!<br /><br />Taran, proud and stubborn as youth:<br /><br /><i>'I told you to swim clear. Are all Assistant Pig-Keepers deaf as well as stubborn?'<br /><br />'I don't know how to swim!' Taran cried, his teeth chattering violently.<br /><br />'Then why did you not say so before we started across?'<br /><br />'I was sure I could learn,' Taran protested. <b>'As soon as I came to do it.</b> If Melyngar hadn't sat on me . . .'</i><br /><br />And talkative Eilonwy, with her smartass tricks and witty banter:<br /><br /><i>'You mean you live in this terrible place?’ Taran asked.<br /><br />‘Naturally. You don't imagine I'd want to visit here, do you?’</i><br /><br />And she knows archery too? This book was published in the 60s, so a smart, badass, well-ahead-of-her-time (you should listen to her take on things) heroine was a delight!<br /><br />And Doli, adorably not-as-disagreeable-as-he-pretends-to-be, the dwarf.<br /><br /> And I'm a sucker for humour of course.<br /><br /><i>'Coll!' Taran cried. 'Not the same . . .'<br />'The same.'<br />'But . . . but . . .' Taran stammered. 'Coll? A hero? <b>But . . . he's so bald!'</b></i><br /><br /><br />Fun adventure, filled with humour, characters that you can't help but care for, and a bit of darkness that makes for some great character development.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7529010844279376859" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


